TextEng: I'd like to ask you some questions.
Do you know what's going on in Luskan?
Text: 러스칸에서 무슨 일이 벌어지고 있는지 알아?

TextEng: I'm looking for work, if you know of any.
Text: 일거리를 찾고 있어. 혹시 아는 거 있어?

TextEng: You know what goings on in city?
Me look for job. You got one?
Where can I go to buy equipment and supplies?
Text: 장비랑 물자는 어디서 살 수 있어?

TextEng: Maybe I could ask you something else.
Why do you need the ring?
Can't you just buy it from her?
Why you not just buys it from her?
I have some more questions about this job.
Text: 이 일에 대해 질문이 좀 더 있어.

TextEng: Any chance I could get an advance on this job?
Me want money up front to do this.
Why do you need the ring?
Tell me again where I can find Lady Jadale.
Text: 자데일 부인을 어디서 찾을 수 있는지 다시 말해 줘.

TextEng: You say again where Lady be.
I want to ask you again about getting the ring for you.
Text: 반지 가져다주는 일에 대해 다시 물어보고 싶어.

TextEng: Me want ask you again 'bout getting ring for you.
Text: 나 반지 가져다주는 거 다시 물어볼래.

TextEng: You mentioned something about a job before.
I have the ring right here.
I seem to recall some mention of a reward?
You said you give reward for ring.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> It wasn't easy to get this, you know. I think you could spare a little more.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이거 구하기 쉽지 않았거든. 좀 더 줄 수 있지 않아?

TextEng: You better cough up some more coin or you won't even live long enough to regret it!
Text: 돈 더 내놔. 안 그러면 후회할 시간도 없이 죽을 거야!

TextEng: Thanks - it's been a pleasure doing business with you.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Me work hard for this. You give more gold, yes?
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 나 이거 힘들게 구했어. 금화 더 줘, 응?

TextEng: Me want more gold! Give more or you be sorry and you be dead!
Text: 나 금화 더 원해! 더 줘 안 그러면 후회해 그리고 죽어!

TextEng: Me happy - me like work for you.
Text: 나 기뻐. 나 너랑 일하는 거 좋아.

TextEng: I suppose the reward is adequate.
Surely you could spare more for a fellow gnome?
Text: 같은 노움한테 좀 더 줄 수 있지 않아?

TextEng: You give me more cause we both be gnome, 'kay?
Text: 우리 둘 다 노움이니까 더 줘, 응?

TextEng: You're one of the brothel's men?
Uhh... you was chest con-... con-oh...
I've never heard of a place called Culver.
